HEADWORD: Agglomerative
<hw>Ag*glom"er*a*tive</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a
tendency to gather together, or to make collections.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Taylor is eminently discursive, accumulative, and (to use one of
his own words) <qex>agglomerative</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Agglutinant</ent>⟦br⟧
